# O.C. Tanner
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** employee recognition / corporate culture / HR technology
**Website:** https://www.octanner.com

## Overview
O.C. Tanner is a global leader in employee recognition and workplace culture solutions. The company designs, develops, and delivers recognition programs, survey tools, and consulting services that help organizations improve employee engagement, retention, and performance. Its cloud-based platform, Culture Cloud, enables managers and peers to give meaningful, timely recognition and rewards to employees.

Founded in 1927 as a small recognition jewelry manufacturer, O.C. Tanner has evolved into a comprehensive culture technology company. Today it serves more than 6,000 clients worldwide, including many Fortune 500 companies. The company’s research arm, the O.C. Tanner Institute, publishes annual studies such as the “Global Culture Report,” which provides data-driven insights on workplace trends and employee experience.

O.C. Tanner matters because it addresses a fundamental challenge in modern organizations: how to build a culture where people feel valued, connected, and motivated. Its programs and platforms are used by millions of employees to recognize one another, reinforcing positive behaviors and fostering a sense of belonging that directly impacts business outcomes.

## Utah connection
O.C. Tanner was founded and is headquartered in Salt Lake City, Utah. The company is one of the state’s most prominent privately held enterprises and a pillar of the local business community. Its corporate campus in downtown Salt Lake City includes a visitor center, museum, and manufacturing facility. O.C. Tanner has also contributed significantly to Utah’s philanthropic landscape through the Obert C. and Grace A. Tanner Foundation, which supports arts, education, and humanities programs along the Wasatch Front. The company’s presence helped establish Utah as a hub for human resources technology and cultural strategy innovation.

## Key people
- **Obert C. Tanner** (1904–1993) – Founder. A noted philanthropist, educator, and businessman who started the company as a small trophy and award business.
- **David Buss** – Chief Executive Officer (as of 2025). Formerly President of the company, Buss leads O.C. Tanner’s global strategy and product development.
- **Chad Stringham** – Chief Marketing Officer. Oversees brand, research, and client engagement, including the O.C. Tanner Institute’s annual reports.